Revision history for Langertha-Skeid

{{$NEXT}}

    - Initial release extracted from Knarr
    - Add Langertha::Skeid control-plane module for dynamic node/pricing config
    - Add normalized metrics + cost helpers via Knarr Input/Output/Metrics APIs
    - Add Langertha::Skeid::Proxy (OpenAI + Anthropic + Ollama routes)
    - Add weighted routing, inflight/max_conns admission, and node health control
    - Add usage_store support with sqlite and postgresql backends
    - Add SQL schema files: sql/usage_events.sqlite.sql and sql/usage_events.postgresql.sql
    - Add request usage recording and summary reporting (usage.record / usage.report)
    - Add skeid CLI subcommand: `skeid usage` for quick usage/cost readout
    - Add configurable saturation wait behavior:
      routing.wait_timeout_ms + routing.wait_poll_ms (429 after timeout)
    - Make proxy request path non-blocking with Mojolicious async upstream calls
      and non-blocking route wait polling (parallel request friendly)
    - Add dzil post-release Docker build+push flow for `raudssus/langertha-skeid`
      (`%v`, major, and `latest` tags)
    - Normalize Skeid engine IDs to Langertha class naming (lowercase)
      and reject legacy aliases like `openai-compatible`
    - Use `Langertha->available_engine_ids` for engine discovery when available,
      so Skeid follows the same core/LangerthaX engine registry as Langertha
    - Tighten runtime dependency minimum versions in cpanfile:
      `Langertha 0.307`, `Langertha::Knarr 0.006`
    - Add dynamic admin route protection:
      `/skeid/*` returns 404 without admin key and requires bearer auth when set
    - Dockerfile: add optional `LANGERTHA_SRC` and `KNARR_SRC` build args to
      inject unreleased sources when CPAN indexers lag
    - dist.ini release Docker build supports optional
      `SKEID_DOCKER_BUILD_ARGS='...'` passthrough for temporary build overrides,
      including GitHub release-dist URL examples and a note against
      `/archive/refs/*` source archives for dzil dists
    - dist.ini now uploads `Langertha-Skeid-%v.tar.gz` to GitHub releases
      (`Getty/langertha-skeid`) via `gh` during post-release hooks
    - dist.ini now runs `${GH_BIN:-gh}` directly in separate
      `run_after_release` steps (no pre-check, no chained `&&`), so hooks use
      invoking-shell runtime environment/path
